point_name_eng: The breath passes the area of ST11, located next to the Trachea

acupoint_code: ST36 is the lower sea point)
ST36 regulates 3 things; ST, SP and KID. Some sources say the upper, middle and lower heaters.
ST38 is located between the lower sea points of the CO and SI. This point is likened to the small opening between these 2 organs
point_name_eng: 8 cun under the tibio – femoral joint line, 1 fingerbreadth from the tibia, halfway between the tibio – femoral joint line and the external malleolus

acupoint_code: ST40 is located at the center of the shin. As a stomach point it has earth CHI, which is the element, associated with the center. As a Lou point it has abundant earth CHI
point_name_eng: 8 cun under the knee crease, 2 fingerbreadths from the tip of the tibia

acupoint_code: HT6 is the Xi - cleft point of heart. Yin is a reference to the Shao Yin
point_name_eng: Radial to the flexor carpi ulnaris, 0.5 cun from the wrist crease

acupoint_code: HT6 dispersed + HT9 dispersed for epilepsy from wood disturbing heart.

SI11 and HT have a direct connection. This point is located near he Shu point of HT. The heavens are above and the heart is known as the organ that rules from above. Both the heavens and the heart have functions of higher/celestial power.
point_name_eng: SI11 is a point where CHI accumulates.

acupoint_code: The 5th point on the BL meridian

The 2 heads of the trapezius muscle are like two pillars supporting the head (heaven). BL10 is located on these pillars. Pillars are also a reference to the spinal vertebra in ancient times they were called “Tian Zhu”
point_name_eng: 1.3 cun lateral to GV15, on the lateral sides of the trapezius, levels with the L.B.S.P. (lower border spinal process) of C-1
Shu of Sacrum and Central Backbone

acupoint_code: BL54 is the last point on the lateral line of the BL meridian before it continues to flow behind the leg. It is the lower border of the sequence, which began at BL41
point_name_eng: 3 cun lateral to the midline of the back, at the height of the 4th sacral foramen

acupoint_code: BL58 is the Lou point of the BL where the meridian attaches to the KID. From here the CHI disperses from the yang side to the yin side of the leg. This is where yang (BL) is dispersed to yin (KID)
point_name_eng: 7 cun above BL60 half way between the posterior midline of the leg and the posterior border of the tibia

acupoint_code: BL66 is located near the tip of the KID meridian. After CHI passes through BL67-KID1 it arrives at the shining valley (KID2). BL66 is located on the other side of the valley. It is the spring point of the BL meridian. This point is likened to a passage through a tunnel helping the CHI flow through to the stream point and eventually to the He – sea point.
point_name_eng: At the lateral aspect of the foot, in the notch distal and inferior to the 5th metatarsal phylange bone, where the skin color changes

acupoint_code: BL67 is the final point on the BL meridian (a yang meridian). From here the CHI flows to the KID meridian
point_name_eng: At the lateral aspect of the 5th toe 1 fen proximal and lateral to the corner of the fingernail

acupoint_code: KID1 is located at the “earth” portion of the foot from a Chinese cosmological perspective. From this point water flows up like a spring. The first point on the kidney meridian is a bubbling spring for the entire body. Because of its location, this is the point with the strongest connection to earth, where the body pulls/nurses Yin
point_name_eng: In the depression formed at the sole of the foot when it is in plantar flexion, 1/3rd of the way from the base of the 2nd toe to the tip of the heel, between the 2nd and 3rd metatarsal bones, proximal to the metatarsal phalanx bones.

acupoint_code: KID3 is found in the depression that is likened to a valley that gathers water from the mountains. From here the water continues to flow until a river is formed which eventually flows to the sea.
KID5 is the Xi – cleft point on this meridian. It is located in a crevice where the CHI/water of the kidney is gathered.
point_name_eng: 1 cun inferior to KID3 in the slight depression anterior and superior to the medial aspect of the bump of the achilles

acupoint_code: KID12 directs the influence of the Chong, which crosses through the KID meridian at this point
TH1, HT9 and PC9 all have the character Chong in their names to express the flowing, bursting motion of CHI that they contain
point_name_eng: At the ulnar aspect of the 4th finger, 1 fen proximal to the corner of the nail
Diagonal in the direction of the meridian 1 cun
7. Balances body weight, promotes weight loss

acupoint_code: TH22 connects TH to SI and GB. The ear bones working in harmony form the shape of a kidney. The kidneys open up to the ears. When the kidneys are harmonized the ears can hear the 5 tones
point_name_eng: Level with the root of the ear, anterior and superior to TH21

acupoint_code: CV4 is the passage of Yuan CHI.” The critical meeting of original yang and original yin take place here. It is the storage place of Yuan CHI.
point_name_eng: On the midline of the abdomen 2 cun above CV2

acupoint_code: CV7 is a yin cross roads. Here KID, CV and Chong meet up. It is located on the yin aspect of the body
point_name_eng: On the abdominal midline 4 cun above CV2

acupoint_code: GV7 is the point of rotation at the center of the spine. GV 5,6, and 7 are similar in their names and functions
point_name_eng: On the back midline, at the lower border of T10

acupoint_code: GV15 is connected to the root of the tongue. It used to treat speech/voice disorders
point_name_eng: On the midline of the neck, between C1 and C2, 0.5 cun inferior to GV16, level with BL10

acupoint_code: CO4 is contraindicated throughout pregnancy. This is due to its strong yang quality which can cause contractions. For this same reason, it is also a very effective point during labor.
point_name_eng: Ren6 is contraindicated because of its location

acupoint_code: BL23 and DU4 are both contraindicated because of their locations. Also, DU4 has a strong energetic effect on the kidneys and BL23 has a strong connection with the DAI MAI, both systems should be used cautiously during pregnancy.
point_name_eng: A pregnant woman who is very weak should not be needled.

acupoint_code: The 8 extraordinary meridians are opened by using both a “master” and “couple” point. To allow for a good treatment one must follow a few basic rules
point_name_eng: Master points are needled on the left side on men and on the right for women.

acupoint_code: BL11 – HUI meeting of the bones.
point_name_eng: BL13 – SHU meeting point of the lungs

acupoint_code: BL14 – SHU point of the pericardium
point_name_eng: BL15 – SHU point of the heart

acupoint_code: BL16 – SHU point of the DU Mai
point_name_eng: BL17 – HUI meeting point of the blood and SHU point of the diaphragm

acupoint_code: BL18 – SHU point of the liver
point_name_eng: BL19 – SHU point of the gall bladder

acupoint_code: BL20 – SHU point of the spleen
point_name_eng: BL21 – Shu point of the stomach

acupoint_code: BL22 – Shu point of the triple burner
point_name_eng: BL23 – SHU point of the kidneys

acupoint_code: BL24 – SHU point of the sea of CHI
point_name_eng: BL25 – SHU point of the large intestine

acupoint_code: BL26 – SHU point of the gate of vitality
point_name_eng: BL27 – SHU point of the small intestine

acupoint_code: BL28 – SHU point of the urinary bladder
point_name_eng: BL29 – SHU point of the sacrum

acupoint_code: BL30 – SHU point of the anus

point_name_eng: These points are important in understanding the physiology of the Tendo Muscular Meridians. The TMM, via these points, can stop a pathogen which has made its way into the body from further penetrating. We can tonify the defensive CHI at these areas using the TMM meeting points.
